Claims CLAIMS  What is claimed is: 1. A blinding tube assembly for concealing a drug delivery tube having a tubular dispensing stem, the assembly comprising: a blinding tube comprising: a tubular sleeve having a first end with an access opening formed thereat and an opposing second end, the sleeve having an interior surface at least partially bounding a compartment; and a tubular dispersing stem projecting from the second end of the tubular sleeve, the dispersing stem bounding a passage extending therethrough; and a tubular bushing having a first end configured to be received within the passage of the dispersing stem and having an interior surface that bounds a throughway, the throughway being configured to receive the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube such that when the drug delivery tube is received within the compartment of the blinding tube, the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube can be fluid coupled to the dispersing stem of the blinding tube through the bushing. 2. The blinding tube assembly of claim 1, wherein the dispersing stem of the blinding tube comprises: an annular sidewall having an interior surface extending between a first end and an opposing second end, the first end being coupled with the tubular sleeve, the interior surface at least partially bounding a channel; and a terminal end face disposed at the second end of the sidewall so as to cover a portion of the channel, a dispersing opening extending through the terminal end face so as to communicate with the channel, the passage of the dispersing stem comprising the channel and the dispersing opening. 3. The blinding tube assembly of claim 2, wherein the bushing comprises: a tubular body that bounds a cavity; and 

 an annular flange radially inwardly extending from the tubular body so as to cover a portion of the cavity, the flange encircling a transfer opening that communicates with the cavity, the throughway of the bushing comprising the cavity and the transfer opening. 4. The blinding tube assembly of claim 3, wherein the dispersing opening has a diameter that is smaller than a diameter of the transfer opening. 5. The blinding tube assembly of claim 3, further comprising a cap removably connected to the dispersing stem of the blinding tube. 6. A blinding tube system comprising: a blinding tube comprising: a tubular sleeve having an interior surface at least partially bounding a compartment and that extends between a first end and an opposing second end; and a dispersing stem projecting from the second end of the tubular sleeve, the dispersing stem bounding a passage extending therethrough and communicating with the compartment; and a drug delivery tube housing a dosage and having a dispensing stem through which the dosage can pass, the dispensing stem terminating at an annular end face, the drug delivery tube being received within the compartment of the blinding tube with the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube being coupled with the dispersing stem of the blinding tube. 7. The blinding tube system of claim 6, wherein the annular end face of the dispensing stem is not visible through the dispersing opening of the dispersing stem from outside the blinding tube. 8. The blinding tube system of claim 6, further comprising a tubular bushing disposed between the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube and the dispersing stem of the blinding tube. 9. The blinding tube system of claim 6, wherein the dispersing stem of the blinding tube comprises: an annular sidewall having an interior surface extending between a first end and an opposing second end, the first end being coupled with the tubular sleeve, the interior surface at least partially bounding a channel, the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube being received within the channel; and a terminal end face disposed at the second end of the sidewall so as to cover a portion of the channel, a dispersing opening extending through the terminal end face so as to communicate with channel, the passage of the dispersing stem comprising the channel and the dispersing opening. 10. The blinding tube system of claim 9, wherein the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube has a dispensing opening extending therethrough, the dispensing opening having a diameter that is larger than a diameter of the dispersing opening of the blinding tube. 11. The blinding tube system of claim 9, further comprising a bushing encircling the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube and being received within the channel of the dispersing stem. 12. The blinding tube system of claim 11, wherein the bushing comprises: a tubular body that bounds a cavity, the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube being received within the cavity; and an annular flange radially inwardly extending from the tubular body so as to cover the annular end face of the dispensing stem, the flange encircling a transfer opening that communicates with the cavity. 13. A method of assembling a blinding tube system, comprising: inserting a delivery end of a drug delivery tube into a compartment of a blinding tube through an access opening at a first end of the blinding tube, the drug delivery tube housing a dosage and having a tubular dispensing stem through which the dosage can pass, the blinding tube having a second end opposite the first end with a dispersing stem projecting therefrom; 

 advancing the drug delivery tube within the compartment of the blinding tube until the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube couples with the dispersing stem of the blinding tube; and closing the access opening at the first end of the blinding tube so that the drug delivery tube is concealed within the blinding tube. 14. The method of claim 13, further comprising: the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube terminating at an annular end face; and the dispersing stem of the blinding tube having a passage extending therethrough, the dispensing stem coupling with the dispersing stem so that an end face of the dispensing stem is not visible through the passage of dispersing stem from outside the blinding tube. 15. The method of claim 13, wherein the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube terminating at an annular end face, the method further comprising coupling the dispensing stem with the dispersing stem so that the dispersing stem covers the end face of the dispensing stem. 16. The method of claim 13, further comprising: attaching a bushing to the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube before inserting the delivery end of a drug delivery tube into the compartment of the blinding tube; and the bushing engaging the blinding tube to produce the coupling between the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube and the dispersing stem of the blinding tube when the drug delivery tube is advanced into the compartment of the blinding tube. 17. The method of claim 13, wherein the step of advancing comprises advancing the drug delivery tube within the compartment of the blinding tube until the dispensing stem of the drug delivery tube couples with the dispersing stem of the blinding tube through a tubular bushing disposed therebetween. 18. The method of claim 13, wherein the step of closing the access opening at the first end of the blinding tube comprises crimping or rolling the first end of the blinding tube. 19. The method of claim 13, further comprising threadedly coupling a cap onto the dispersing stem of the blinding tube.
